graph.Title: LIST OF SYNAPSES, HERMAPHRODITE AND MALE, CHEMICAL AND GAP JUNCTIONAL  These files give the properties of all the synapses scored.  The contin number ("contin" = a connected set of database objects representing a structure that may "continue" across several sections) together with the EM series designation give each synapse a unique identifier.  They may be found on a neuron map at WormWiring.org using this identifier.  For chemical polyads, the order of the postsynaptic cells given in column D and H-K is the clockwise order the cells were scored around the presynaptic density on the electron micrographs.  As the micrograph images are viewed consistently looking towards anterior, so that left and right sides of the image correspond to left and right sides of the worm, this clockwise ordering orients the postsynaptic arrangement in the worm.
